rtain to appeal to both union and business leaders, this volume also offers crucial insights to policy makers and to scholars of the new American workplace.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aIndustrial organizationzUnited States. 0aLaborzUnited States. 0aManufacturing industrieszUnited States. 0aWork environmentzUnited States. 4aLabor History. 4aSocial Work. 4aSociology & Social Science.1 aBatt, Rosemary, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172064240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501720642423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501720642/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles